@Node "Intro" "Introduction"
@Prev "Copy"
@Next "Req"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  AGA-Morph is a so called morphing program. It calculates a picture out of
  a starting, an end picture and some more or less precise positioned
  points, representing a morph between them.

  Thanks to:
    Robert den Broeder
      For the correction of the english  documentation and his Ideas, that
      have not been completely included.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Req" "Requirements"
@Prev "Intro"
@Next "Feat"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  What do you need to use AGA-Morph?

   - Amiga with kickstart 3.0 or better.
   - AGA-chipset or graphic board with emulation.

  This program has been tested on an Amiga 4000 with kickstart 3.0
  Please send bugs or suggestions to the Author.
  Use at your own risk.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Feat" "Features"
@Prev "Req"
@Next "Install"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

Version V2.1 of AGA-Morph includes:

 - Morphing in 24-Bit
 - Loading via Datatypes or 24-bit-Iff
 - Saving in 24-bit-Iff
 - Pictures up to the size of 65535x65535 (or your memory)
 - GUI in english or german
 - Runs on any Screenmode (some gfx-problems with lores)
 - 040-FPU, 040, 020-FPU, 020, FPU and 68000 version
 - Completely written in C

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Install" "Installation"
@Prev "Feat"
@Next "Start"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  There are two installation scripts available.
   - Install for english
   - Install-d for german

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Start" "Starting"
@Prev "Install"
@Next "Requester"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  At the  beginning of  the program you will  be asked to  select a screen-
  mode, therefor a  @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} will be opened. Please select  a mode
  with at least  640 times 400  pixels, otherwise  you can't  see the whole
  screen.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Requester" "systemrequester"
@Prev "Start"
@Next "Menu"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The use of the systemrequesters is  explained in your workbench- or dos-
  manual.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

