@Node "Menu0.0" "Load Picture 1"
@Prev "Menu"
@Next "Picture"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will load a picture into the @{"Picturebuffer" Link "Picture"} 1. The picture
  will be  loaded in  either  24bit  (iff-picture)  of via  the datatypes.
  Therefor a @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} for files will be opened.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Picture" "Picturebuffer"
@Prev "Menu0.0"
@Next "Menu0.1"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  There are 3 different picture buffers:
   - for the starting picture of the morph (picture 1)
   - for the end picture of the morph (picture 2)
   - for the rendered picture

  All buffers work  in 24bit and  at a maximum  resolution  of 65535 times
  65535 points. picture 1  and picture 2 can only  be loaded, the rendered
  picture can only be saved.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.1" "Load Picture 2"
@Prev "Picture"
@Next "Menu0.2"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will load a picture into the @{"Picturebuffer" Link "Picture"} 2. The picture
  will be  loaded in  either  24bit  (iff-picture)  of via  the datatypes.
  Therefor a @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} for files will be opened.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.2" "Load Points"
@Prev "Menu0.1"
@Next "Menu0.3"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will load the points that  are needed for the later rende-
  ring. Therefor a @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} for files will be opened.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.3" "Save Picture"
@Prev "Menu0.2"
@Next "Menu0.4"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will  save the rendered  picture out of  the corresponding
  @{"picturebuffer" Link "Picture"}. Therefor a @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} for files will be opened.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.4" "Save Points"
@Prev "Menu0.3"
@Next "Menu0.5"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will  save the points  that are needed for  the rendering.
  Therefor a @{"systemrequester" Link "Requester"} for files will be opened.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.5" "Dest. Pic. [320]x[256]"
@Prev "Menu0.4"
@Next "Menu1.0"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The size of the picture  to be rendered will be  shown/changed here. You
  can change the size by just selecting the gadget and entering the wanted
  size. The maximum for both values here is 65535.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.0" "Change Points 1"
@Prev "Menu0.5"
@Next "Menu1.1"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The points of picture 1 will be selected to be changed. The change it-
  self will take place in the @{"editwindow" link "Edit"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.1" "Change Points 2"
@Prev "Menu1.0"
@Next "Menu1.2"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The points of picture 2 will be selected to be changed. The change it-
  self will take place in the @{"editwindow" link "Edit"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.2" "Change Spline"
@Prev "Menu1.1"
@Next "Menu1.3"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The points of the spline will be  selected to be changed. The change it-
  self will take place  in the @{"editwindow" link "Edit"}. But here  not only the points,
  but also the splines will be shown.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.3" "New Point"
@Prev "Menu1.2"
@Next "Menu1.4"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will insert  a new point  @{u}after@{uu} the  @{"selected" Link "Menu1.5"} point. This
  new point will now be the selected one.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.4" "Delete Point"
@Prev "Menu1.3"
@Next "Menu1.5"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function deletes  the @{"selected" Link "Menu1.5"} point. The  point after the deleted
  one will be the new selected point.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.5" "Selected Point [  0]"
@Prev "Menu1.4"
@Next "Menu2.0"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  The selected point will be shown/changed  with this gadget. 0 means that
  no point is  selected. If you enter a  number higher than  the number of
  points, it will be automatically be set to the maximum.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.0" "% of 2nd Picture"
@Prev "Menu1.5"
@Next "Menu2.1"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  You can change the  percentage of the second  picture with this gadget. 0
  percent means  only the pixels  of the first  picture will  be used, 100
  percent means only the pixels of the second picture will be used.
  This number will influence the corresponding @{"scrollbar" Link "Menu2.1"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.1" "% of 2nd Picture (scrollbar)"
@Prev "Menu2.0"
@Next "Menu2.2"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  You can change the percentage of the  second picture with this scrollbar.
  0 percent means only  the pixels of the first picture  will be used, 100
  percent means only the pixels of the second picture will be used.
  Its number will be shown in the corresponding @{"gadget" Link "Menu2.0"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.2" "% of 2nd Points"
@Prev "Menu2.1"
@Next "Menu2.3"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  You can change  the percentage of the second points  with this gadget. 0
  percent means  the shape of the first  picture will  not be shifted, 100
  percent means the shape of the second picture will not be shifted.
  This number will influence the corresponding @{"scrollbar" Link "Menu2.3"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.3" "% of 2nd Points (scrollbar)"
@Prev "Menu2.2"
@Next "Menu2.4"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  You can change the percentage of the second points with this scrollbar. 0
  percent means  the shape of the first  picture will  not be shifted, 100
  percent means the shape of the second picture will not be shifted.
  Its number will be shown in the corresponding @{"gadget" Link "Menu2.2"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.4" "Spline On/Off"
@Prev "Menu2.3"
@Next "Menu2.5"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function  toggles the spline rendering  on or off.  Spline rendering
  means the shifting of the shape will  be calculated with the help of the
  spline points. Splines off means the shifting of the shape will be calcu-
  lated with a straight line.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.5" "Render Picture"
@Prev "Menu2.4"
@Next "Menu3.0"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function will start the rendering of the picture corresponding to
  the given parameters and points. A bar will be displayed in the middle of
  the screen to show the progress of the rendering. After the rendering is
  complete the picture will automatically be shown in the view window.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.0" "Show Picture 1"
@Prev "Menu2.5"
@Next "Menu3.1"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function shows the picture of the @{"picturebuffer" Link "Picture"} 1 in the view
  window.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.1" "Show Picture 2"
@Prev "Menu3.0"
@Next "Menu3.2"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function shows the picture of the @{"picturebuffer" Link "Picture"} 2 in the view
  window.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.2" "Show rendered Picture"
@Prev "Menu3.1"
@Next "Menu3.3"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function shows the  rendered picture of the  @{"picturebuffer" Link "Picture"} in
  the view window.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.3" "AGA-Morph V2.1 Info"
@Prev "Menu3.2"
@Next "Menu3.4"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function opens the info window where free and used memory will
  be displayed and the size of the pictures. Also the address of the
  author and his picture will be shown.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.4" "4xZoom On/Off"
@Prev "Menu3.3"
@Next "Menu3.5"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function toggles the  4 times zoom  for the edit  and the view
  window on and off.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu3.5" "Quit"
@Prev "Menu3.4"
@Next "Menu0.6"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function quits the program.  Warning all data  will be lost if
  it has not been saved.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu0.6" "Delete all Points"
@Prev "Menu3.5"
@Next "Menu1.6"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  This function not only deletes all points.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu1.6" "Reset Splines (Esc)"
@Prev "Menu0.6"
@Next "Menu2.6"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  With this function you can delete @{u}all@{uu} spline points (after this they will
  be exactly between the  two other points). This  function is only avail-
  able if you have selected the spline to be changed and they are shown in
  the @{"edit window" Link "Edit"}.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

@Node "Menu2.6" "Change Colors (Space)"
@Prev "Menu1.6"
@Next "Menu3.6"
@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}

  With this function you can change the color of the points and the mouse.

   - Grey    * (Mouse: 101010 808080 f0f0f0) (Point: 171717 7f7f7f d7d7d7)
   - Red       (Mouse: 100000 800000 f00000) (Point: 170000 7f0000 d70000)
   - Green     (Mouse: 001000 008000 00f000) (Point: 001700 007f00 00d700)
   - Blue      (Mouse: 000010 000080 0000f0) (Point: 000017 00007f 0000d7)
   - Yellow    (Mouse: 101000 808000 f0f000) (Point: 171700 7f7f00 d7d700)
   - Magenta   (Mouse: 100010 800080 f000f0) (Point: 170017 7f007f d700d7)
   - Cyan      (Mouse: 001010 008080 00f0f0) (Point: 001717 007f7f 00d7d7)

  * means default.
  The colors are given in hexadecimal RRGGBB.

@{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}                                                @{b}@{fg shine}AGA-Morph V2.1@{ub}@{fg text}
@Endnode

